Install Roles and Features

Role - Something Windows Server aspires to be. Where the machine you want it to go/functions you want Windows to support.

Role Service - Functions that fulfill a particular aspiration for that server. These must be installed for a particular role.


Feature - Everything else on the server.


Server Core is what Windows wants to use. Get used to this.

If you close out of cmd prompt accidentally in Core, hit ctrl + alt + del again.

Some GUI panels still available
  Task Manager
  notepad
  timedate.cpl

Use sconfig.cmd to access cmd prompt-type menu to configure windows.

Powershell not the default shell when logging in.
